**concerns:**
- Asset 404s in thumbnails: the test deck references external assets (cover-bg.jpg, founder images, etc.) that don't exist at the temp copy location, so iframe thumbnails 404 on images. Styled text/content still renders; this is acceptable under the "decorative-failure rule" but may look incomplete in screenshots.
- Deck chip UI persistence: `loadDeckIntoTray` sets `tray.setLibrary(null)` but does not hide the `#deck-chip` DOM element. If a user later loads a library, the deck chip remains visible alongside the library chip. Pre-existing UI behavior, not introduced here.
- No row-kind DOM differentiation: deck rows and library rows are structurally identical in the rendered DOM. Future compose tasks (p3-1) may need to add `data-kind` attributes or CSS classes for visual/behavioral distinction.

